1. DEFINITIONS

   "Software" refers to Bijmantra, including all source code, documentation,
   assets, and associated files in this repository.
   
   "Creator" refers to Denish Dholaria and R.E.E.V.A.i (Rural Empowerment 
   through Emerging Value-driven Agro-Intelligence).
   
   "You" refers to any individual or organization using, copying, modifying,
   or distributing the Software.
   
   "Commercial Use" means any use of the Software where the Software itself,
   or access to the Software, is sold, licensed for a fee, or bundled with
   products or services sold for profit.
   
   "Internal Use" means use of the Software within an organization for that
   organization's own operations, regardless of whether the organization is
   for-profit or non-profit.
   
   "For-Profit Agricultural Company" means any corporation, partnership, or
   business entity engaged in commercial seed production, seed sales, crop
   breeding for profit, agricultural biotechnology, or related agribusiness
   activities that generates revenue exceeding $1,000,000 USD annually.
   
   "Well-Funded Institution" means any university, research institution, or
   organization with an annual operating budget or endowment exceeding
   $100,000,000 USD.

