================================================================================
       SECTION 2A: FOR-PROFIT AGRICULTURAL COMPANY REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

For-Profit Agricultural Companies (as defined in Section 1) are subject to
the following additional requirements:

2A.1 COMMERCIAL LICENSE OBLIGATION

   For-Profit Agricultural Companies with annual revenue exceeding
   $1,000,000 USD that use the Software for ANY purpose — including
   internal breeding operations, research, data management, or product
   development — MUST obtain a Commercial License within one hundred
   eighty (180) days of first deployment.

2A.2 RATIONALE

   Large agricultural corporations derive substantial commercial benefit
   from breeding software, even when used internally. The varieties they
   develop using such tools generate significant profits. This provision
   ensures that those who profit most from agricultural innovation
   contribute fairly to the tools that enable their success.

2A.3 REVENUE THRESHOLDS

   (a) $1,000,000 - $10,000,000 USD annual revenue:
       Commercial License fee of $2,500 USD per year
   
   (b) $10,000,000 - $100,000,000 USD annual revenue:
       Commercial License fee of $10,000 USD per year
   
   (c) $100,000,000 - $1,000,000,000 USD annual revenue:
       Commercial License fee of $25,000 USD per year
   
   (d) Over $1,000,000,000 USD annual revenue:
       Commercial License fee of $50,000 USD per year OR 0.01% of
       annual revenue attributable to breeding operations, whichever
       is greater

2A.4 EXEMPTIONS

   The following For-Profit Agricultural Companies are EXEMPT from
   Section 2A requirements:
   
   (a) Companies headquartered in countries classified as "Low Income"
       or "Lower Middle Income" by the World Bank
   
   (b) Companies where more than 50% of revenue is derived from sales
       to smallholder farmers (defined as farms under 5 hectares)
   
   (c) Companies that have made qualifying donations under Section 3A

================================================================================
                      SECTION 3: COMMERCIAL LICENSE TERMS
================================================================================

3.1 EVALUATION PERIOD

   Commercial entities may evaluate the Software for up to ninety (90) days
   without a Commercial License. After the evaluation period, You must either:
   
   (a) Cease Commercial Use, or
   (b) Obtain a Commercial License from the Creator

3.2 COMMERCIAL LICENSE FEES (General)

   For uses described in Section 2 (excluding Section 2A):
   
   (a) SAAS/HOSTED SERVICES: 10% of gross subscription revenue attributable
       to the Software
   
   (b) SOFTWARE SALES: 15% of gross revenue from sales of the Software or
       derivative works
   
   (c) BUNDLED PRODUCTS: Negotiated on a case-by-case basis
   
   (d) MINIMUM ANNUAL FEE: $1,000 USD per year (or equivalent in local
       currency), regardless of revenue

3.3 STARTUP GRACE PERIOD

   Startups with less than $100,000 USD in annual revenue may use the
   Software commercially for up to two (2) years without payment. After
   the grace period, or upon exceeding the revenue threshold, standard
   Commercial License terms apply.

3.4 DISCOUNTS

   (a) DEVELOPING COUNTRIES: Organizations headquartered in countries
       classified as "Low Income" or "Lower Middle Income" by the World
       Bank receive a 50% discount on Commercial License fees
   
   (b) PUBLIC BREEDING PROGRAMS: Government-funded and CGIAR breeding
       programs are exempt from Commercial License requirements

3.5 HOW TO OBTAIN A COMMERCIAL LICENSE

   Contact the Creator:
   
   Email: denishdholaria@gmail.com
   Subject: "Bijmantra Commercial License Inquiry"
   
   Include: Your organization name, intended use, and estimated revenue

================================================================================
         SECTION 3A: VOLUNTARY DONATIONS AND SPONSORSHIP
================================================================================

3A.1 SUSTAINABILITY STATEMENT

   Bijmantra is developed and maintained by an independent creator who
   depends on this work for livelihood. Continued development, bug fixes,
   security updates, and new features require sustained financial support.
   
   While the Software is freely available for many uses, the Creator
   encourages organizations that benefit from the Software to consider
   voluntary financial contributions to ensure its long-term sustainability.

3A.2 DONATION ENCOURAGEMENT FOR WELL-FUNDED INSTITUTIONS

   Well-Funded Institutions (as defined in Section 1) — including major
   universities, agricultural research centers, and foundations — are
   STRONGLY ENCOURAGED to make voluntary donations commensurate with
   their financial capacity and the value derived from the Software.
   
   Suggested donation levels for Well-Funded Institutions:
   
   (a) Institutions with $100M - $500M annual budget:
       Suggested donation of $1,000 - $5,000 USD per year
   
   (b) Institutions with $500M - $1B annual budget:
       Suggested donation of $5,000 - $15,000 USD per year
   
   (c) Institutions with over $1B annual budget or endowment:
       Suggested donation of $15,000 - $50,000 USD per year
   
   These are VOLUNTARY suggestions, not requirements. However, institutions
   that make qualifying donations will receive:
   
   • Priority support and feature requests
   • Recognition on the Bijmantra website and documentation
   • Early access to new features and releases
   • Direct communication channel with the Creator

3A.3 CORPORATE SPONSORSHIP

   For-Profit Agricultural Companies may offset Commercial License fees
   through corporate sponsorship arrangements, including:
   
   (a) Direct financial sponsorship
   (b) Developer time contributions (valued at market rates)
   (c) Infrastructure support (hosting, CI/CD, etc.)
   (d) Research partnerships
   
   Contact the Creator to discuss sponsorship arrangements.

3A.4 DONATION METHODS

   Donations may be made via:
   
   • GitHub Sponsors: https://github.com/sponsors/denishdholaria
   • Direct bank transfer (contact for details)
   • Cryptocurrency (contact for wallet addresses)
   • Institutional grants or research funding allocations
   
   All donations are gratefully acknowledged unless anonymity is requested.

3A.5 TRANSPARENCY

   The Creator commits to publishing an annual transparency report
   detailing:
   
   • Total donations and sponsorships received
   • How funds were used (development, infrastructure, etc.)
   • Roadmap priorities influenced by sponsors
   
   This report will be published on the project website and repository.

